Comment: 0,0:01:37.78,0:01:37.82,Sign,,0,0,0,,{chapter}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:38.95,0:01:43.49,Default,,0,0,0,,Thanks to mother and Luise, \Nwho rushed all the way from Munich,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:43.49,0:01:46.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Lotte's illness was gone \Nbefore you can say Jack Robinson.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:47.69,0:01:49.45,Default,,0,0,0,,A once-in-a-lifetime chance - {unique; matchless; unparalleled; unparallelled; never again​}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:49.45,0:01:52.87,Default,,0,0,0,,"Dad and his partner should definitely reconcile,"
Dialogue: 0,0:01:52.87,0:01:56.80,Default,,0,0,0,,was the new aim that Luise and her partner \Nset their sights on.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:58.60,0:02:05.71,Default,,0,0,0,,In turn, father and mother also realized that the schism \Nin their feelings was caused by a simple misunderstanding. {difference of opinion; misunderstanding; estrangement; disagreement}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:05.71,0:02:07.35,Default,,0,0,0,,One last push!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:07.78,0:02:12.15,Default,,0,0,0,,That's when the unforeseen complication takes place.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:13.05,0:02:18.05,Sign,,0,0,100,,{\c&HEAFCF9&\bord0\blur0.8\fs20}Episode 26 \N {\fs35} Saying Goodbyes? No! {サヨナラなんて、いや!} \N\N\N\N\N\N\N\N\N\N\N {\fs23} \h Translation: Perevodildo | Timings: Sub-RoRo \h
Dialogue: 0,0:02:20.16,0:02:24.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Today, I come here with an important favor to ask.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:24.10,0:02:27.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Ah, about that? Unfortunately, let me see...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:28.86,0:02:30.35,Default,,0,0,0,,We have an emergency, Herr Palfy!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:30.35,0:02:32.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Becker? What is it? You look flustered. {to become confused (disconcerted, disorganized, disorganised); to be flustered; to panic}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:32.47,0:02:37.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Just a moment ago, our leading actress \NYvonne Janowitz suddenly got hospitalized!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:37.50,0:02:38.44,Default,,0,0,0,,What are you saying?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:38.84,0:02:41.48,Default,,0,0,0,,The director wants to see you immediately. {shihainin is likely "manager; executive" but hitsei after it - no clue}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:41.48,0:02:43.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Got it. I'll go there right away.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:44.51,0:02:45.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Apologies, Frau Irene.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:45.94,0:02:47.72,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll call you some time later.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:47.72,0:02:48.89,Default,,0,0,0,,Herr Palfy!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:52.06,0:02:53.19,Default,,0,0,0,,My!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:54.51,0:02:57.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Things look dire. \NShould either postpone or cancel the concert. {/can't be helped}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:57.73,0:02:59.20,Default,,0,0,0,,No, no, Herr Palfy.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:59.20,0:03:03.57,Default,,0,0,0,,If I were you, I would have considered \Na postponement or a cancellation unfavorable. {good policy; wise policy; best plan}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:03.57,0:03:05.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Isn't that so, Becker?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:05.17,0:03:06.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:06.90,0:03:11.74,Default,,0,0,0,,There already exists an unfortunate streak of two concerts - \Nin Berlin and in Munich - cancelled one after another. {one after the other; successively}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:11.74,0:03:17.07,Default,,0,0,0,,If this concert ends in a cancellation as well, \Nit may deal a fatal blow to your reputation in media. {/what do we say to ...}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:17.07,0:03:19.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Never mind the media. \NThey don't understand a thing.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:19.54,0:03:23.99,Default,,0,0,0,,Here's what I think, why don't we double down \Nand reassign the leading role{, just this one time}? {he doesn't say reassign cause I duuno what he originally meant: here, one resolutely; boldly; decisively; daringly, don't go to leading role}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:24.85,0:03:25.99,Default,,0,0,0,,You're thinking Lenz?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:27.98,0:03:30.52,Default,,0,0,0,,It's true that there's an undeniable potential to her.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:30.52,0:03:32.56,Default,,0,0,0,,But making it until tomorrow...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:32.56,0:03:35.96,Default,,0,0,0,,If we don't push it to the extremes, \Nwe might arrive to a pitiful fiasco. {I have not a single clue what he originally meant: if we don't to take good care of; to treasure; to value; to hold dear; to prize; to cherish, when she/it returns/goes home, it may become poor/miserable}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:35.96,0:03:40.36,Default,,0,0,0,,It will be all right. \NI know her, and I have faith in her.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:40.36,0:03:41.83,Default,,0,0,0,,As well as in you. {/because you'll be the one doing it}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:45.42,0:03:47.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's go for it, Herr Palfy!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:47.14,0:03:48.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Can't know until you try!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:48.94,0:03:49.81,Default,,0,0,0,,Fine, then.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:50.21,0:03:51.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Tell everyone to gather on the stage.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:51.94,0:03:52.81,Default,,0,0,0,,Roger!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:55.48,0:03:56.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Ah?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:56.62,0:03:58.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, my bad! I've forgotten.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:59.28,0:04:03.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Becker, sorry to bother you, \Nbut I need you to go to Cafe Schubert for me.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:03.42,0:04:06.96,Default,,0,0,0,,There, find a woman by the name of Körner \Nand tell her this from me, {to convey; to report; to transmit; to communicate; to tell; to impart; to propagate; to teach; to bequeath}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:06.96,0:04:09.63,Default,,0,0,0,,"Today, I have some urgent matters to tend to." {/I can't go due to these circumstances.}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:09.63,0:04:12.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Understood. Miss Körner, isn't that right?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:12.60,0:04:14.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, counting on you.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:14.16,0:04:16.33,Default,,0,0,0,,Herr Palfy, everyone's ready.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:19.22,0:04:20.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Körner?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:21.41,0:04:22.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Could it be...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:29.18,0:04:32.39,Default,,0,0,0,,You're his manager, Herr Becker, isn't that right?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:32.39,0:04:32.99,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:32.99,0:04:37.72,Default,,0,0,0,,The message you were just asked you to convey - \NI'm actually acquainted to that person.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:37.72,0:04:40.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Is that so? \NThen, would you do it for me?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:40.19,0:04:43.13,Default,,0,0,0,,This place is currently a kerfuffle, \Nyou'd really help us out! {confusion; disorder; mess; muddle​}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:56.45,0:04:57.92,Default,,0,0,0,,He's quite late.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:01.02,0:05:03.45,Default,,0,0,0,,In the bygone times, \NI would have gone home already. {long ago; a long time ago; already​}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:07.28,0:05:09.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Mom's quite late.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:09.78,0:05:13.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Must be that she's chatting to dad heartily.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:13.72,0:05:15.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Leaving us two out?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:15.32,0:05:18.95,Default,,0,0,0,,Right. Make no mistake, \Nit's an important talk just for two.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:19.34,0:05:20.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Then, you think they're...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:20.84,0:05:22.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Definitely, Luise.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:27.55,0:05:29.68,Default,,0,0,0,,The dream is coming true!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:31.09,0:05:33.72,Default,,0,0,0,,In five days from now, it's our birthday.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:33.72,0:05:35.59,Default,,0,0,0,,We'll celebrate it as a family of four!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:35.59,0:05:36.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Right!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:37.31,0:05:38.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Of four!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:48.30,0:05:50.37,Default,,0,0,0,,Is this Frau Körner I'm seeing?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:51.47,0:05:52.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:52.54,0:05:56.00,Default,,0,0,0,,You may know me as a certain Irene Gerlach.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:00.34,0:06:06.28,Default,,0,0,0,,It appears, dad have been seeing some woman \Nnamed Irene Gerlach quite frequently.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:06.98,0:06:08.45,Default,,0,0,0,,You mind if I join you?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:09.25,0:06:10.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Not at all...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:14.72,0:06:16.03,Default,,0,0,0,,May I take your order?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:16.03,0:06:16.93,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll have Sherry.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:16.93,0:06:17.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Sure.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:20.40,0:06:25.90,Default,,0,0,0,,As a matter of fact, Herr Palfy intended \Nto come here personally to introduce me.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:25.90,0:06:29.37,Default,,0,0,0,,But then, some others matters \Ndemanded his immediate attention.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:30.67,0:06:34.34,Default,,0,0,0,,If that's how {\i1}she{\i0} puts it, \Nit must really be so. {really not sure who she means, maybe "what should I say when talking to that woman" or "so that's the woman I was told about" or w/e}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:35.35,0:06:39.82,Default,,0,0,0,,In addition, we two were planning \Nto celebrate our engagement here. {goaisatsu is "greeting; greetings; salutation; salute; condolences; congratulations​" and I've no clue what she means, maybe "announce"?; also she says "only/just to me" and idk what this means either}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:40.52,0:06:41.81,Default,,0,0,0,,Engagement?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:41.81,0:06:46.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh my... You were never informed up to now?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:46.40,0:06:49.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, that's Herr Palfy for you.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:49.60,0:06:52.73,Default,,0,0,0,,The other day, he made a solemn proposal to me.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:53.52,0:06:54.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Proposal?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:57.63,0:07:00.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Ah, in that case, accept my congratulations.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:00.70,0:07:02.83,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:02.83,0:07:05.80,Default,,0,0,0,,But I must apologize, too! \NWe made you wait for so long.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:05.80,0:07:11.07,Default,,0,0,0,,You know him - when it comes to music, \Nit's like the rest of the world can wait.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:11.84,0:07:13.68,Default,,0,0,0,,This is so troublesome.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:16.01,0:07:20.78,Default,,0,0,0,,However, out of deference for his music, \Nwe could forgive him this little oversight.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:22.23,0:07:27.17,Default,,0,0,0,,After all, his genius is probably \Nthe God's gift to humanity. {lit: that man, used by god in this world, genius - not sure what she means, also has the meaning of "to use (a person, animal, puppet, etc.); to employ; to handle; to manage; to manipulate"}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:27.17,0:07:30.56,Default,,0,0,0,,He does all that to bestow \Nmore of his amazing music upon us. {to give (esp. to someone of lower status); to bestow; to grant; to confer; to present; to award}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:31.07,0:07:36.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Personally, I intend to prop up Herr Palfy \Nin all his endeavors, whatever they might be. {to put to use; to make good use of; to exploit}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:36.14,0:07:41.51,Default,,0,0,0,,For that purpose, I'm going to leverage my father's \Nnumerous influential connections in the most diverse fields. {lit: among dad's acquintances, from every quarter; all sides, there are people who have influence; clout; leverage, in big numbers}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:54.72,0:07:55.76,Default,,0,0,0,,However...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:57.73,0:08:02.98,Default,,0,0,0,,I believe, nothing surpasses in importance \Nbeing understanding and caring towards your partner.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:02.98,0:08:07.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Even when the world of music \Ninfatuates him to the point where he stops looking at you,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:07.17,0:08:10.87,Default,,0,0,0,,it's best that you step away \Nand let him roam it freely. {to spread one's wings; to go out into the world}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:11.34,0:08:13.54,Default,,0,0,0,,My, a piece of educated portending? {sermon; preaching; homily}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:13.54,0:08:18.37,Default,,0,0,0,,Rest assured. I have my own ways \Nof conferring my love on him. {And quite effective ones at that. } {unsure what she emeans: I love him in my own manner/way of doing it}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:19.11,0:08:21.62,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm so sorry! \NI didn't mean to say that... {/said too much}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:22.28,0:08:24.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Well then, may you both be happy.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:37.73,0:08:39.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Bon voyage, sweetheart. {adieu; farewell; bon voyage}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:47.74,0:08:50.38,Default,,0,0,0,,How could I actually be that foolish?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:51.29,0:08:52.85,Default,,0,0,0,,An unforgivable mistake. {/I was impossibly wrong}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:15.04,0:09:16.29,Default,,0,0,0,,Mom!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:17.34,0:09:19.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Welcome back. Where's dad?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:21.85,0:09:25.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Lotte, how come you forgot to mention it?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:25.61,0:09:29.08,Default,,0,0,0,,The fact your father \Nand Frau Gerlach are engaged.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:30.22,0:09:32.42,Default,,0,0,0,,He isn't! It was one big misunderstanding! {/something's wrong here}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:32.42,0:09:33.99,Default,,0,0,0,,Dad wasn't being serious!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:34.93,0:09:37.46,Default,,0,0,0,,So you knew, but didn't tell me either, Luise.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:41.31,0:09:44.20,Default,,0,0,0,,That's something you two \Nshould have mentioned earlier.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:44.20,0:09:46.80,Default,,0,0,0,,I should now congratulate your father, shouldn't I?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:47.60,0:09:48.84,Default,,0,0,0,,I protested it!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:52.73,0:09:56.24,Default,,0,0,0,,My own mom... \NIs the only mom for me!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:56.91,0:09:58.91,Default,,0,0,0,,Mom, will you really let it slide?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:58.91,0:10:02.22,Default,,0,0,0,,You think it's fine for dad to marry Frau Gerlach?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:03.82,0:10:08.26,Default,,0,0,0,,As long as it makes your dad happy, \Nit's the finest thing ever.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:11.66,0:10:16.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Your dad's unhappiness \Nis something I want to avoid seeing at any cost. {/I don't want to see ... ever again}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:17.08,0:10:19.37,Default,,0,0,0,,Dad's unhappiness?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:20.44,0:10:25.81,Default,,0,0,0,,Having attended some more of your dad's concerts \Nafter we broke up, I've been able to discern it clearly -
Dialogue: 0,0:10:27.54,0:10:30.58,Default,,0,0,0,,his wound had been much deeper than mine.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:31.00,0:10:35.44,Default,,0,0,0,,But attending his concerts even after you broke up, \Nmeans you loved him still, didn't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:35.44,0:10:38.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Even now, you're still very fond of dad, aren't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:43.08,0:10:44.45,Default,,0,0,0,,It's too late.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:45.79,0:10:47.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Way too late.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:12.78,0:11:13.88,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm sorry.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:14.95,0:11:18.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Your mom had overstayed her welcome here. {/can't stay here any longer}
Dialogue: 0,0:11:33.27,0:11:34.43,Default,,0,0,0,,Mom?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:35.40,0:11:36.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Mom?!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:40.92,0:11:42.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Resi, where's mom?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:43.02,0:11:45.29,Default,,0,0,0,,It would appear to me that she went out.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:46.15,0:11:47.32,Default,,0,0,0,,But where to?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:47.92,0:11:50.19,Default,,0,0,0,,That letter might hold some keys to it.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:54.97,0:11:58.40,Default,,0,0,0,,"I just remembered about some job \NI absolutely need to get done.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:58.40,0:12:00.59,Default,,0,0,0,,I shall return to Munich now.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:00.59,0:12:02.53,Default,,0,0,0,,My best regards to your father.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:02.53,0:12:04.17,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll call you soon."
Dialogue: 0,0:12:04.81,0:12:05.87,Default,,0,0,0,,But why?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:06.47,0:12:10.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Did it without even saying goodbyes to us! {last night}\NThis is so unlike her...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:10.11,0:12:11.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Resi, has dad been here?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:11.75,0:12:13.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Nope, not to my knowledge.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:13.71,0:12:15.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Sleeping in his atelier, perhaps?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:16.08,0:12:17.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Lotte, we'll call him right away!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:35.49,0:12:36.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Not there.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:36.47,0:12:40.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, right! I think, he conducts a concert \Nin the Opera House today.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:40.13,0:12:41.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Must be there!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:41.27,0:12:42.40,Default,,0,0,0,,On our way, then!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:46.51,0:12:48.42,Default,,0,0,0,,We can't see our dad?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:48.42,0:12:53.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Regret to say it, but I can't help you. \NI'm instructed to not let in anyone but the staff. {/concerned person}
Dialogue: 0,0:12:53.98,0:12:56.85,Default,,0,0,0,,But we're here for a reason! {/important business}\NCan't we peek in just for a second?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:57.28,0:13:01.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Today, it's explicitly forbidden. \NThe director looked mighty stern, ordering this.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:01.35,0:13:06.23,Default,,0,0,0,,I know! You can try writing a note, \Nand I'll see if I can pass it at some point.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:07.48,0:13:08.68,Default,,0,0,0,,What now?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:08.68,0:13:11.57,Default,,0,0,0,,I feel that it's something \Nwe need to ask dad directly.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:12.13,0:13:13.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Are you {\i1}absolutely{\i0} sure?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:14.77,0:13:16.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Sorry, girls.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:16.58,0:13:18.24,Default,,0,0,0,,I see...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:18.91,0:13:20.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Thanks for your service.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:31.63,0:13:33.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Hey... Hold it, Fraulein!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:33.50,0:13:35.93,Default,,0,0,0,,Off-limits for anyone but the staff!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:35.93,0:13:37.26,Default,,0,0,0,,That won't be a problem. {/don't worry - damn, this is where translating "concerned parties" as staff comes back to bite me in the as}
Dialogue: 0,0:13:37.26,0:13:39.97,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm the fiancee of Herr Palfy himself.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:40.73,0:13:43.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Hey, wait! No, you'll get me in trouble!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:46.26,0:13:48.30,Default,,0,0,0,,OK! Let's take a short break.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:48.30,0:13:50.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Intermission - one hour!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:50.74,0:13:53.85,Default,,0,0,0,,Lenz, this one was perfect just now. \NKeep up the good work.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:53.85,0:13:55.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you very much!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:55.35,0:13:58.68,Default,,0,0,0,,But in the final aria of the first act, \Ntry to restrain your emoting. {/you should restrain/control your emotions more}
Dialogue: 0,0:13:58.68,0:13:59.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:59.32,0:14:02.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Conductor, would you be able to listen to me \Nduring this intermission for a bit?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:02.82,0:14:03.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Sure, no problem.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:05.29,0:14:06.79,Default,,0,0,0,,Herr Palfy!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:08.43,0:14:09.79,Default,,0,0,0,,Frau Irene?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:09.79,0:14:12.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Could I confer with you for a few minutes \Nabout our mutual affairs?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:12.82,0:14:15.23,Default,,0,0,0,,I'd be glad to, but some other time, please.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:15.23,0:14:16.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Hey, Becker!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:17.19,0:14:19.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Herr Palfy! This is an urgent matter!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:19.90,0:14:21.77,Default,,0,0,0,,Becker, do you know where director is?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:21.77,0:14:23.43,Default,,0,0,0,,Holding a conference in the next room.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:25.81,0:14:28.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Director, could you summon Schwarz here as well?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:29.19,0:14:30.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Herr Palfy!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:30.82,0:14:32.84,Default,,0,0,0,,It's about the accompaniment for Lenz's aria. {lit: lenz-kun's aria's accompaniment - not sure what he means}
Dialogue: 0,0:14:32.84,0:14:34.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Understood, I'll arrange it immediately. {again, lit is "immediately, prerapations" - no clue}
Dialogue: 0,0:14:34.71,0:14:38.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Herr Palfy, I need to ask you \Nabout the engagement announcement party...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:38.28,0:14:39.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Becker!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:39.15,0:14:39.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:39.62,0:14:43.06,Default,,0,0,0,,For one hour starting now,\Nsee that our practice is uninterrupted. {lit: after this, for one hour, in the midle of practice, make is off-limits; restricted; forbidden for me - no clue yet again, it's the same wording the guards used to deny girls the entrance earlier, but why'd palfy say it if the whole theater is sealed already? maybe he means don't let the musicians out? but why now, during the break and only for an hour and why he says during the practice if it's intermission? beats me}
Dialogue: 0,0:14:43.46,0:14:44.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Understood.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:45.24,0:14:46.86,Default,,0,0,0,,What should I do about your meal? {maybe he asks "what should I get you" maybe "what do the musicians do about eating, then?" (in relation to the previous line, somehow)}
Dialogue: 0,0:14:48.43,0:14:50.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Later. Not until Lenz's aria is polished. {/I need to listen to ... first}
Dialogue: 0,0:14:51.28,0:14:53.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Herr Palfy, the date for the ceremony...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:53.10,0:14:55.97,Default,,0,0,0,,Actually, director! \NI'd like to do some parts of the second act, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:55.97,0:14:57.41,Default,,0,0,0,,Summon Meyer as well. {Meyer is marked as "architect from gerlach's party" but I suppose it's the other one}
Dialogue: 0,0:14:57.41,0:14:59.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Very well. Anyone else?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:59.35,0:15:01.09,Default,,0,0,0,,No need, that's enough for now.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:01.09,0:15:04.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Herr Palfy, we also need to finish choosing the dress! {/order}
Dialogue: 0,0:15:04.34,0:15:05.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Becker, what else is in the program? {lit: remaining plans; arrangement; schedule; program; programme; expectation; estimate}
Dialogue: 0,0:15:05.78,0:15:07.24,Default,,0,0,0,,One more rehearsal in the evening.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:07.24,0:15:07.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Got it.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:10.01,0:15:12.48,Default,,0,0,0,,That's quite rude, Herr Palfy!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:12.48,0:15:15.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Between me and the opera, \Nwhich one is more important to you?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:17.81,0:15:22.63,Default,,0,0,0,,The most important thing is being understanding \Nand caring towards your partner.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:22.63,0:15:25.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Be it even at the expense \Nof him paying attention to you. {/even if, for example, he no longer looks at you}
Dialogue: 0,0:15:28.44,0:15:30.78,Default,,0,0,0,,It's not something I can't figure out myself.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:38.84,0:15:39.95,Default,,0,0,0,,Not there?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:51.27,0:15:52.53,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm sorry.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:52.93,0:15:56.78,Default,,0,0,0,,If I hear your voices right now, \NI'll break into tears!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:03.55,0:16:05.04,Default,,0,0,0,,What's going on?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:05.04,0:16:08.45,Default,,0,0,0,,I know! Editor-in-Chief is the one \Nwho might have some leads.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:13.79,0:16:15.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes? Bernau on the phone.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:16.78,0:16:20.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, Luise? Is Lotte feeling all right?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:22.42,0:16:23.59,Default,,0,0,0,,About your mother?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:24.49,0:16:26.36,Default,,0,0,0,,No, we've not seen her in the office.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:27.00,0:16:28.87,Default,,0,0,0,,Ah, I got it! \NI'll try looking into it. {/look for her}
Dialogue: 0,0:16:29.20,0:16:30.37,Default,,0,0,0,,Worries aside.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:30.37,0:16:32.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you, it'd be of great help.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:34.06,0:16:37.93,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't worry. When Editor-in-Chief finds her, \Nwe'll know everything.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:37.93,0:16:39.34,Default,,0,0,0,,What a relief!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:48.38,0:16:54.82,Default,,0,0,0,,With Herr Palfy, I can excuse a lot for the sake of music, \Nbut the way he treated me today... Does he have any limits? {cruel treatment; raw deal; kick in the pants​ was a bit too much}
Dialogue: 0,0:16:54.82,0:16:56.75,Default,,0,0,0,,I ought to have a word with him about it. {to say; to tell; to state; to express; to offer; to extend (greetings, congratulations, etc.)​ at least a word}
Dialogue: 0,0:17:01.41,0:17:07.53,Default,,0,0,0,,If today's concert is not plagued with contingencies, \NHerr Palfy's reputation would be once again on its peak.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:07.53,0:17:12.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Right. I'm also concerned about how'd it go, \Nafter that streak of disasters he had lately.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:12.48,0:17:19.45,Default,,0,0,0,,But say, during the daytime rehearsal, Herr Palfy had \Nthis look on his face, saying "don't get in my way, or else..." {lit: had a impressiveness; impact; force; intensity; appeal; strength; punch; edge; vigor that was bloodcurdling; ghastly}
Dialogue: 0,0:17:19.94,0:17:21.52,Default,,0,0,0,,That is very true.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:21.52,0:17:25.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Even while Frau Gerlach was clinging to him, \Nit was as though she is is invisible to him!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:26.85,0:17:28.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Right, right.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:28.15,0:17:32.32,Default,,0,0,0,,At times like that, Herr Palfy \Nis pretty much deaf and blind, not just to her.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:32.32,0:17:38.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's say, the president himself suddenly shows up - \NPalfy still wouldn't condescend to look at him.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:41.80,0:17:47.07,Default,,0,0,0,,The most important thing \Nis being understanding and caring towards your partner.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:47.07,0:17:50.92,Default,,0,0,0,,When he flies off to the world of music, \Nyou don't try to restrain him.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:52.11,0:17:55.45,Default,,0,0,0,,Even if he ends up completely forgetting to look at you.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:57.88,0:18:01.82,Default,,0,0,0,,I have a feeling that Fraulein Lenz \Nhad some of Herr Palfy's passion rubbed off on her,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:01.82,0:18:04.53,Default,,0,0,0,,so we should expect \Na terrific leading role performance. {as was expected; just as one thought; sure enough - not sure}
Dialogue: 0,0:18:06.46,0:18:11.63,Default,,0,0,0,,It's true what they say about Palfy - \Nmust be that his genius is the God's gift to humanity!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:31.46,0:18:31.99,Default,,0,0,0,,My...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:32.57,0:18:34.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Hey. Welcome back.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:35.14,0:18:37.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Editor, but why?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:37.26,0:18:40.36,Default,,0,0,0,,I didn't feel like dining alone tonight.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:40.36,0:18:41.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Would you keep me company?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:44.06,0:18:45.39,Default,,0,0,0,,The girls sent you, didn't they?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:46.04,0:18:50.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Leading two adorable Frauleins a merry dance - \N quite unbecoming of you.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:50.30,0:18:54.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Come on, need to defeat my growling stomach now. \NI'll hear your explanations later. {having a meal (before doing something); fortifying oneself with a meal}
Dialogue: 0,0:18:57.97,0:19:01.95,Sign,,0,0,0,,The wretch now thou knowest, {Or sai chi l'onore}
Dialogue: 0,0:19:02.98,0:19:07.35,Sign,,0,0,0,,Who sought my betraying, {Rapire a me volse,}
Dialogue: 0,0:19:07.85,0:19:11.99,Sign,,0,0,0,,And vengeance thou owest {Chi fu il traditore}
Dialogue: 0,0:19:12.55,0:19:21.33,Sign,,0,0,0,,My father's, my father's foul slaying. {Che il padre mi tolse.}
Dialogue: 0,0:19:21.33,0:19:25.58,Sign,,0,0,0,,For justice I sue thee; {Vendetta ti chiedo,}
Dialogue: 0,0:19:26.43,0:19:31.51,Sign,,0,0,0,,I ask of thy troth... {La chiede il tuo cor.}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:11.45,0:20:12.29,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm home!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:21.43,0:20:23.02,Default,,0,0,0,,But why, so suddenly...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:23.47,0:20:25.67,Default,,0,0,0,,We're the ones asking that!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:25.67,0:20:28.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Dad, did you say anything to mom?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:28.27,0:20:30.97,Default,,0,0,0,,Last night, she went to Cafe "Something," \Nto see you, didn't she?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:30.97,0:20:31.74,Default,,0,0,0,,No...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:32.38,0:20:34.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Yesterday, I was too busy... {unsure he means this}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:35.18,0:20:37.00,Default,,0,0,0,,It's your fault!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:37.00,0:20:39.44,Default,,0,0,0,,It's because you didn't show up! {unsure, maybe she means "You did something unacceptable/mistreated her"}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:39.44,0:20:40.54,Default,,0,0,0,,I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:41.04,0:20:43.88,Default,,0,0,0,,She must've been waiting until the very end. And then...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:44.25,0:20:45.92,Default,,0,0,0,,...Mom returned home,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:46.82,0:20:50.36,Default,,0,0,0,,when she found out you're marrying Frau Gerlach!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:51.89,0:20:54.66,Default,,0,0,0,,This is unthinkable! \NUnnatural and unthinkable!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:54.66,0:20:57.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Dad, we only wish... We only wish...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:57.46,0:20:59.36,Default,,0,0,0,,...That our dad and mom...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:59.36,0:21:01.30,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}reconcile!{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:21:21.92,0:21:29.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Just as they were this close to opening their hearts, \Nfather and mother end up parting ways again.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:30.30,0:21:34.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Lotte and Luise can't help wondering, \N"Is our dream really coming true?"
Dialogue: 0,0:21:35.49,0:21:41.74,Default,,0,0,0,,As well as, "Will we be able to finally come together \Nto celebrate our birthday as a family of four?"
Comment: 0,0:21:58.47,0:21:58.47,Sign,,0,0,0,,{chapter}
Dialogue: 0,0:22:04.41,0:22:07.94,Sign,,0,0,0,,A miserable romance {可哀想ね　ロマンス}
Dialogue: 0,0:22:07.94,0:22:11.40,Sign,,0,0,0,,A tear-jerking nuance {涙誘うニュアンス}
Dialogue: 0,0:22:11.40,0:22:15.12,Sign,,0,0,0,,If you turn another page of your memories, {想い出のページめくれば}
Dialogue: 0,0:22:15.12,0:22:18.03,Sign,,0,0,0,,Here she is - heroine of the past {追憶のヒロイン} {actually, "the heroine of the recollections" but that doesn't have a nice ring to it}
Dialogue: 0,0:22:26.25,0:22:29.67,Sign,,0,0,0,,I raise my eyes to your face - {あなたの面影　見上げて咲いている}
Dialogue: 0,0:22:29.67,0:22:33.43,Sign,,0,0,0,,Suddenly, I'm in full bloom {unsure, maybe "it's flourishing"}
Dialogue: 0,0:22:33.43,0:22:36.97,Sign,,0,0,0,,A sunflower amidst the blizzard - {act. in the middle of winter}
Dialogue: 0,0:22:36.97,0:22:40.37,Sign,,0,0,0,,that would be me, my dear {真冬のひまわり　それが私なの}
Dialogue: 0,0:22:40.81,0:22:43.54,Sign,,0,0,0,,Always on the verge of freezing, {凍えるような気持ちでいつも}
Dialogue: 0,0:22:44.39,0:22:46.94,Sign,,0,0,0,,My feelings are out of control -
Dialogue: 0,0:22:46.94,0:22:51.49,Sign,,0,0,0,,Too stiff to even say "Do you still love me?" {「好き?」と尋くこともできず}
Dialogue: 0,0:22:51.49,0:22:55.64,Sign,,0,0,0,,My lips just keep wavering in this wind! {風に揺れていたわ}
Dialogue: 0,0:22:57.19,0:23:00.84,Sign,,0,0,0,,A pitiful Romance {いじらしいね　ロマンス}
Dialogue: 0,0:23:00.84,0:23:04.25,Sign,,0,0,0,,Something that only happens in dreams - {夢のような出来事}
Dialogue: 0,0:23:04.25,0:23:07.88,Sign,,0,0,0,,Trying hard to forget, I fell even more in love {忘れるために愛したの}
Dialogue: 0,0:23:07.88,0:23:10.65,Sign,,0,0,0,,with heroine of the past {追憶のヒロイン}
Dialogue: 0,0:23:11.70,0:23:15.47,Sign,,0,0,0,,Miracle that I came across now is hugging me tight {めぐりあえた奇跡　そっと抱きしめて}
Dialogue: 0,0:23:15.47,0:23:18.88,Sign,,0,0,0,,This is the story of my life, my duty is to protect it! {私だけの歴史　守ってゆくわ}
Comment: 0,0:23:22.47,0:23:22.47,Sign,,0,0,0,,{chapter}
Dialogue: 0,0:23:22.79,0:23:24.34,Sign,,0,0,0,,Next episode
Dialogue: 0,0:23:27.01,0:23:32.75,Sign,,0,0,0,,Eh? No way it's true? Lotte should also return to Munich? \NDid mom really said so?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:32.75,0:23:35.39,Sign,,0,0,0,,I guess she wants to return \Nto our old life as soon as possible. {very unsure, if I hadn't known the context, I'd think she means "I want to ..."}
Dialogue: 0,0:23:35.39,0:23:37.22,Sign,,0,0,0,,And I also have to go to school.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:37.22,0:23:39.69,Sign,,0,0,0,,So mom said, "return tomorrow," just like that.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:39.69,0:23:42.66,Sign,,0,0,0,,I hate it! I can't part with Lotte yet!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:42.66,0:23:45.73,Default,,0,0,0,,I hate it, too! I'm not parting with Luise!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:46.09,0:23:47.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Next time, I and Myself:
Dialogue: 0,0:23:47.96,0:23:50.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Two People, One Wish. {/only one wish per two} {たったひとつの二人の願い}
Dialogue: 0,0:23:49.33,0:23:52.53,Sign,,0,0,0,,Episode 27 \NTwo People, One Wish {/only one wish per two} {たったひとつの二人の願い}
Dialogue: 0,0:23:50.20,0:23:51.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't miss it!
